Problem 3(b):
{x | x1 = 0}

Solution:
The set S = {x | x1 = 0} is a subspace. Suppose x1, x2 ∈S. Then
y = x1 + x2;
y1 = 0 =⇒y ∈S
and let α ∈R
z = αx1;
z1 = 0 =⇒z ∈S
Since the set is closed under addition and scalar multiplication, it is a subset of Rn.

A ∈Fm×n, B ∈Fm×n
R(A + B) = {(A + B)x : x ∈Fn}
= {Ax + Bx : x ∈Fn}
⊆{Ax : x ∈Fn} + {Bx : x ∈Fn}
= R(A) + R(B)
Hence rank(A + B) ≤dim(R(A) + R(B))
Let B1, B2 be basis for R(A) and R(B) respectively. Then B1 ∪B2 spans R(A) +
R(B). Hence dim(R(A) + R(B)) ≤rank(A) + rank(B).
Hence rank(A + B) ≤rank(A) + rank(B)
